China’s Ministry of Public Security on Wednesday decided to launch a 10-month special operation to crack down on abduction and trafficking of women and children.
The ministry said the campaign would be starting from March 1 amid efforts to better protect these groups.
Special efforts should be made to identify woman and child vagrants and beggars, as well as those who are mentally challenged or have verbal and hearing disabilities with unknown origins.
